withoutconditionsseenewenlightenmentUWC7"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"deconstruction","starred":false,"content":"deconstruction has privileged place in Humanities, place of irredentist resistance > principle of civil disobedience, dissidence in name of law above laws, justice of thought","locations":{"raw":"pp. 207-08 ","list":[207,208],"high":208,"low":207},"motif":[{"id":"deconstruction","title":"DECONSTRUCTION"},{"id":"resistance","title":"RESISTANCE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"deconstructionUWC1"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"Derrida links new concept of humanities [a deconstructive one] w/ democratic institution called literature, to a certain simulacrum, a certain “as if”","locations":{"raw":"p. 208 ","list":[208],"high":208,"low":208},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"democracy","title":"DEMOCRACY"},{"id":"literature","title":"LITERATURE"}],"id":"asifasUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"resistance","starred":false,"content":"university w/out conditions as a promise, pledge, a profession of faith","locations":{"raw":"p. 208 ","repeat":true,"list":[208],"high":208,"low":208},"motif":[{"id":"resistance","title":"RESISTANCE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"resistanceUWC6"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"resistance","starred":false,"content":"deconstruct all determined figures sovereignty has taken throughout history","locations":{"raw":"p. 208 ","repeat":true,"list":[208],"high":208,"low":208},"motif":[{"id":"resistance","title":"RESISTANCE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"resistanceUWC5"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"resistance","starred":false,"content":"thought: that which commands resistance","locations":{"raw":"p. 208 ","list":[208],"high":208,"low":208},"motif":[{"id":"resistance","title":"RESISTANCE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"resistanceUWC4"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"“as,” “as if,” politics of the virtual (not a virtual politics) in cyberworld or cyberspace of worldwide-ization > delocalizing, virtualization of communication, publication, archivization","locations":{"raw":"pp. 209-10 ","list":[209,210],"high":210,"low":209},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"derridaspolitics","title":"DERRIDA’S POLITICS "},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"},{"id":"virtual","title":"VIRTUAL"}],"id":"asifasUWC2"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"where there’s trace there’s some virtualization (i.e. virtualization not absolutely novel)","locations":{"raw":"pp. 209-10 ","repeat":true,"list":[209,210],"high":210,"low":209},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"derridaspolitics","title":"DERRIDA’S POLITICS "},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"},{"id":"virtual","title":"VIRTUAL"}],"id":"asifasUWC3"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"“<em>as if</em> the end of work were at the origin of the world”: begin at once at end & at beginning > begin w/ end<em> as if</em> it were the beginning [event or telos?]","locations":{"raw":"p. 209 ","list":[209],"high":209,"low":209},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"beginningintroduction","title":"BEGINNING (INTRODUCTION)"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"telosend","title":"TELOS (END)"}],"id":"asifasUWC1"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"art","starred":false,"content":"“as if”: 1) imagination, utopia 2) Kant’s “as if (<em>als ob</em>)” from <em>Critique of Judgment</em>, points to finality of nature, is neither <em>order of nature</em> nor <em>order of freedom</em> [agent of deconstructive ferment] 3) <em>oeuvres d’art</em>, discursive idealities that define disciplines called Humanities, a subtle displacement of Kant’s idea: art is art not nature, it is free from all constraint/rules <em>as if</em> it were a product of nature","locations":{"raw":"pp. 210-13 ","list":[210,213],"high":213,"low":210},"motif":[{"id":"art","title":"ART"},{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"deconstruction","title":"DECONSTRUCTION"},{"id":"freedom","title":"FREEDOM"},{"id":"nature","title":"NATURE"}],"id":"artUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"capitalism","starred":false,"content":"new technical “stage” of virtualization > the accelerated rhythm/extent/power of capitalization of such virtuality: digitalization, computerization, virtually immediate <em>mondialisation</em> of readability destabilize university habitat, topology of event no longer “campus”","locations":{"raw":"p. 210 ","list":[210],"high":210,"low":210},"motif":[{"id":"capitalism","title":"CAPITALISM"},{"id":"eventmachine","title":"EVENT & MACHINE"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"},{"id":"virtual","title":"VIRTUAL"}],"id":"capitalismUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"america","starred":false,"content":"<em>mondialisation</em> has to go through U.S.","locations":{"raw":"p. 212 ","list":[212],"high":212,"low":212},"motif":[{"id":"america","title":"AMERICA"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"}],"id":"americaUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"impossible attempt to link “as if” to thinking of event: what happens when “taking place” of <em>le travail</em>, when the place itself, becomes virtual, becomes subject to mode “as if”?","locations":{"raw":"p. 213 ","list":[213],"high":213,"low":213},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"topographyplacetopology","title":"TOPOGRAPHY (PLACE, TOPOLOGY)"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"},{"id":"virtual","title":"VIRTUAL"}],"id":"asifasUWC5"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","starred":false,"content":"bear witness: neither practice nor theory; profession, performative, “as if,” fable [etymology of “to speak” <em>fari</em>/<em>phanai</em>]","locations":{"raw":"pp. 214-15 ","repeat":true,"list":[214,215],"high":215,"low":214},"motif":[{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenmentUWC17"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","starred":false,"content":"professor: profession of faith, who will profess in the future? “to make profession of”: promise, <em>declare openly</em>, pledge, engage > exceeds pure techno-scientific knowledge (constative)","locations":{"raw":"pp. 214-15 ","list":[214,215],"high":215,"low":214},"motif":[{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenmentUWC16"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"christianity","starred":false,"content":"work of a worker (<em>travailleur</em>) must be recognized as craft/trade/profession in market (a semantics rooted in socio-ideological history dating back to Christian Middle Ages) > when is there an <em>oeuvre</em>? professor’s authority not based on production of <em>oeuvre</em>","locations":{"raw":"pp. 216-17 ","list":[216,217],"high":217,"low":216},"motif":[{"id":"christianity","title":"CHRISTIANITY"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"oeuvre","title":"OEUVRE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"christianityUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"not every <em>travail</em> an event in itself, doesn’t always produce an <em>oeuvre</em>, not every performative (always authorized by an institutional “as if”) produces <em>oeuvre</em>","locations":{"raw":"pp. 217-18 ","list":[217,218],"high":218,"low":217},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"institution","title":"INSTITUTION"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"oeuvre","title":"OEUVRE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"asifasUWC6"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","starred":false,"content":"act of <em>professing </em>a doctrine is performative, but <em>doctrine</em> is not","locations":{"raw":"p. 218 ","list":[218],"high":218,"low":218},"motif":[{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenmentUWC20"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"oeuvre","starred":false,"content":"Kant sees philosophy (in university) neither as performative nor as producing <em>oeuvre</em>, but professor of philosophy has total freedom > speaks <em>publicly</em>, but only <em>inside</em> university","locations":{"raw":"pp. 219-20 ","list":[219,220],"high":220,"low":219},"motif":[{"id":"oeuvre","title":"OEUVRE"},{"id":"philosophyasaninstitutionacademiauniversity","title":"PHILOSOPHY AS AN INSTITUTION (ACADEMIA, UNIVERSITY)"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"oeuvreUWC2"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","starred":false,"content":"transformation of cyberspace, beyond nation-state borders—renders <em>inside</em> of university even more unimaginable","locations":{"raw":"p. 220 ","list":[220],"high":220,"low":220},"motif":[{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenmentUWC22"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"commitment","starred":false,"content":"absolute immunity of academic type must be protected even if it risks dangerous auto-immunity, even if we must address ourselves to university’s outside > we must commit ourselves in act, in work, in what we make happen w/ events","locations":{"raw":"p. 220 ","list":[220],"high":220,"low":220},"motif":[{"id":"commitment","title":"COMMITMENT "},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"commitmentUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"work not reducible to activity of act or production of product > virtualization of work complicates disproportion btwn production & work","locations":{"raw":"p. 221 ","list":[221],"high":221,"low":221},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"}],"id":"laborworkUWC4"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"work supposes zone of passivity as much as productive activity","locations":{"raw":"p. 222 ","list":[222],"high":222,"low":222},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"}],"id":"laborworkUWC5"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"what we call “professions” tend to be nonmercenary arts, imply testimonial commitment, responsibility under oath (freely declared): physician, lawyer, professor","locations":{"raw":"p. 222 ","repeat":true,"list":[222],"high":222,"low":222},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"oathsermentswearjurer","title":"OATH (<em>serment</em>) / SWEAR (<em>jurer</em>)"}],"id":"laborworkUWC6"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"original sin > introduction of work, expiation would be the end of work","locations":{"raw":"p. 223 ","repeat":true,"list":[223],"high":223,"low":223},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"originalsin","title":"ORIGINAL SIN"}],"id":"laborworkUWC9"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"“as if” [the end of work]: neither sci-fi utopia of Augustine’s “at the end w/out end,” <em>in fine sine fine </em>(Sabbath w/out evening), nor memory of immemorial (nostalgia for earthly paradise)","locations":{"raw":"p. 223 ","repeat":true,"list":[223],"high":223,"low":223},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"}],"id":"asifasUWC8"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"“as if” <em>mondialisation du monde </em>had as its horizon/origin the disappearance of work (<em>travail</em>) [its virtualization] > <em>work</em>, <em>labor</em>, <em>travail</em> have always implied the real, effective (<em>wirklich</em>) [not virtual]——“as if” [the end of work]: neither sci-fi utopia of Augustine’s “at the end w/out end,” <em>in fine sine fine </em>(Sabbath w/out evening), nor memory of immemorial (nostalgia for earthly paradise)","locations":{"raw":"p. 223 ","list":[223],"high":223,"low":223},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"}],"id":"asifasUWC7"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"christianity","starred":false,"content":"<em>mondialisation</em>, unlike “globalization” or <em>Globalisierung</em>, marks a reference to notion of world in a Christian history","locations":{"raw":"p. 224 ","list":[224],"high":224,"low":224},"motif":[{"id":"christianity","title":"CHRISTIANITY"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"}],"id":"christianityUWC1"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"asifas","starred":false,"content":"[re: “as if the end of work were at the origin of the world”] logical skeleton of this “as if” proposition: world & work can’t co-exist, one would have to choose one or the other > the becoming-world of world, <em>mondialisation</em>, often speaks of “end of work”","locations":{"raw":"pp. 224-25 ","list":[224,225],"high":225,"low":224},"motif":[{"id":"asifas","title":"AS IF / AS"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"}],"id":"asifasUWC9"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"difficult to think work (<em>travail</em>) beyond good & evil > activity of work: freedom, life, production, history good; passivity of work: affect, passion, evil, suffering, pain","locations":{"raw":"p. 224 ","list":[224],"high":224,"low":224},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"}],"id":"laborworkUWC10"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"arrival","starred":false,"content":"techno-scientific virtualization of work, the putting-into-common, any “community” [Aristotle’s city] > mutation of taking place of event, of <em>oeuvre—</em>that which <em>arrives</em>","locations":{"raw":"p. 225 ","list":[225],"high":225,"low":225},"motif":[{"id":"arrival","title":"ARRIVAL"},{"id":"communityunavowableinoperativesociusseesocial","title":"COMMUNITY (UNAVOWABLE, INOPERATIVE), SOCIUS see SOCIAL"},{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"},{"id":"mondialatinisation","title":"MONDIALATINISATION"},{"id":"oeuvre","title":"OEUVRE"},{"id":"universitywithoutconditionsseenewenlightenment","title":"UNIVERSITY WITHOUT CONDITIONS (see NEW ENLIGHTENMENT)"}],"id":"arrivalUWC0"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"The University Without Condition ","display":"UWC"},"mid":"laborwork","starred":false,"content":"history of work, “craft,” trade, profession > there are those “w/out work” who want more,  those w/ too much who want less","locations":{"raw":"p. 227 ","list":[227],"high":227,"low":227},"motif":[{"id":"laborwork","title":"LABOR (WORK)"}],"id":"laborworkUWC13"},{"source":{"id":"UWC","title":"